  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Preparedness for response and early action in Malawi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DIPECHO,Natural disasters</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Malawi is frequently affected by hydro-meteorological disasters, mostly floods, storms and droughts. This exacerbates the precarious situation of communities that depend mostly on non sustainable livelihood strategies. Malawi is also under threat of health epidemics (e.g. cholera) and epidemics that affect the crops (e.g. fall armyworm). There is attention for response preparedness, but coordination and infrastructure from national, district towards village level is insufficient.The Action will contribute to the Disaster Risk Management Policy of Malawi (Annex A) and will enhance response capacities at national, district and village level. The Action is in line with the commitments made at the World Humanitarian Summit (WHS) and will invest in anticipating crisis and localisation of aid contribution to the four priorities of the Sendai Framework.The partners will enhance institutional Early Warning/Early Action capacities at national and district level, developing tools, systems and coordination mechanism as well as maximizing the use of data. In Karonga, at community level, the Action will contribute to better response preparedness. School based work will be at the centre of attention. Besides, the community work will include setting up community response teams and improve First Aid skills. The Action will work to develop multi hazard sensitive social protection systems and safety nets. A crisis modifier is aligned with this Action and will be activated to prepare for an emergency and offer first response.</narrative>
  </description>
